Using atom's latest verison, let's say I type something like this:

```
if (true)
  i = 1;
else
  i = 2;
```

And use auto-indentation on this block. It changes it into:

```
if (true)
  i = 1;
  else
    i = 2;
```

This happens at least with C and JavaScript, haven't tried others. To me, the first version that I typed should be correct. Is this considered normal behavior?
